数的工程师。 \n乔布斯不需要会编程会设计电路，但是他有工程师的思维方式，而且从他历次keynote来看，此人做keynote的思维逻辑性极其严密。 其实所谓工程师最重要的素质也就是逻辑思维能力，而乔布斯的逻辑思维能力超过绝大多数的工程师。 \n','2016-08-02 20:31:09',NULL,0,0),(20161037,8,19550380,'> **Jeff Goodell:** Would you explain, in simple terms, exactly what object-\noriented software is?  \n> **Steve Jobs:** Objects are like people. They’re living, breathing things\nthat have knowledge inside them about how to do things and have memory inside\nthem so they can remember things. And rather than interacting with them at a\nvery low level, you interact with them at a very high level of abstraction,\nlike we’re doing right here.  \n> Here’s an example: If I’m your laundry object, you can give me your dirty\nclothes and send me a message that says, “Can you get my clothes laundered,\nplease.” I happen to know where the best laundry place in San Francisco is.\nAnd I speak English, and I have dollars in my pockets. So I go out and hail a\ntaxicab and tell the driver to take me to this place in San Francisco. I go\nget your clothes laundered, I jump back in the cab, I get back here. I give\nyou your clean clothes and say, “Here are your clean clothes.”  \n> You have no idea how I did that. You have no knowledge of the laundry place.\nMaybe you speak French, and you can’t even hail a taxi. You can’t pay for one,\nyou don’t have dollars in your pocket. Yet I knew how to do all of that. And\nyou didn’t have to know any of it. All that complexity was hidden inside of\nme, and we were able to interact at a very high level of abstraction. That’s\nwhat objects are. They encapsulate complexity, and the interfaces to that\ncomplexity are high level.\n\n个Quora的这个问题中看到的：个Quora的这个问题中看到的：[What is object-oriented\nprogramming?__](//link.zhihu.com/?target=http%3A//www.quora.com/What-is-\nobject-oriented-programming)\n\n','\n<blockquote><b>Jeff Goodell:</b> Would you explain, in simple terms, exactly what object-oriented software is?<br><b>Steve Jobs:</b> Objects are like people. They’re living, breathing things that have knowledge inside them about how to do things and have memory inside them so they can remember things. And rather than interacting with them at a very low level, you interact with them at a very high level of abstraction, like we’re doing right here.<br>Here’s an example: If I’m your laundry object, you can give me your dirty clothes and send me a message that says, “Can you get my clothes laundered, please.” I happen to know where the best laundry place in San Francisco is. And I speak English, and I have dollars in my pockets. So I go out and hail a taxicab and tell the driver to take me to this place in San Francisco. I go get your clothes laundered, I jump back in the cab, I get back here. I give you your clean clothes and say, “Here are your clean clothes.”<br>You have no idea how I did that. You have no knowledge of the laundry place. Maybe you speak French, and you can’t even hail a taxi. You can’t pay for one, you don’t have dollars in your pocket. Yet I knew how to do all of that. And you didn’t have to know any of it. All that complexity was hidden inside of me, and we were able to interact at a very high level of abstraction. That’s what objects are. They encapsulate complexity, and the interfaces to that complexity are high level.</blockquote>个Quora的这个问题中看到的：个Quora的这个问题中看到的：<a href=\"//link.zhihu.com/?target=http%3A//www.quora.com/What-is-object-oriented-programming\" class=\" wrap external\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noreferrer\">What is object-oriented programming?<i class=\"icon-external\"></i></a>\n\n','2016-08-02 20:31:09',NULL,0,0),(20161038,15,19550380,'都tm没说到点子上，乔布斯很小就会编程，大概在12岁的时候，乔布斯就再Palo\nAlto的HP实验室，用Basic和APL在历史上第一台“台式计算机”HP9100上编程。之后他在和Woz做Blue\nBox的时候也会编一些简单的程序，比如数频计算器。但在Apple1真正生产出来之后，都没有再专注于编程。\n\n','\n都tm没说到点子上，乔布斯很小就会编程，大概在12岁的时候，乔布斯就再Palo Alto的HP实验室，用Basic和APL在历史上第一台“台式计算机”HP9100上编程。之后他在和Woz做Blue Box的时候也会编一些简单的程序，比如数频计算器。但在Apple1真正生产出来之后，都没有再专注于编程。\n','2016-08-02 20:31:09',NULL,0,0),(20161039,14,19550380,'